        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-15 18:34:30.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nPer \"5.2.4 Constant names\", the variable, \"logger\", should remain as lower case, even though it's declared as \"static final\".  Also, adding \"final\" before every variable makes the code less readable.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "8c22635a5f81292ac89c0b4367bd4b9f949e5afc",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3237,
          "name": "Waqas Ikram",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "waqas.ikram@est.tech",
          "username": "waqas.ikram"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-16 12:13:22.000000000",
        "message": "Uploaded patch set 4.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
      {
        "id": "01bfc9fc62a25986c1e940edbff6974f236fb0d8",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3237,
          "name": "Waqas Ikram",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "waqas.ikram@est.tech",
          "username": "waqas.ikram"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-16 12:15:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n@Jim\n\nHi Jim, Thanks for reviewing my code, I have changed the variable \"logger\" to lower case.\n\nRegarding, \"final\" keyword before every variable. Personally, I like to use the final keyword for the following reasons\n- It makes the intent of the code clearer.\n- Using final enables the IDE and/or compiler to provide warnings/errors if a variable was changed inadvertently.\n- Can provide infpormation to compiler that can lead to better optimization of the code\n- Recommended by recognised Java architects e.g. Robert Simmons  in his book \"Hardcore Java\"\n\nHowever there are also alternative opinions e.g. in \"Clean Code\" by Robert C. Martin who prefers not to use  the final keyword.\n\n@Jim - if the convention is not to use \"final\" keyword i will revert back the \"final\" keyword changes\n\nRegards,\nWaqas",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
      {
